title UK Construction Supply Chain — bespoke craft vs ready to industrialise (March 2023)
style wardley

// ============================================================
// ANCHORS — demand side (government, citizens, finance)
// ============================================================
anchor Government [0.98, 0.78]
anchor Citizens (Homebuyers) [0.97, 0.68]
anchor Mortgage Companies [0.95, 0.85]

// ============================================================
// TIER 1 — user-visible outputs (homes + QA apparatus)
// ============================================================
component Homes (Private & Social) [0.88, 0.55]
component Building Inspection / QA [0.83, 0.72]

// ============================================================
// TIER 2 — planning, design, and construction modes
// ============================================================
component Planning & Building Regs [0.77, 0.66]
component Architecture / Blueprints [0.70, 0.52]

// Construction mode: the central component showing the bespoke→industrial spread
component Construction Mode [0.62, 0.35]

// ============================================================
// TIER 3 — labour, equipment, manufacture
// ============================================================
component Skilled Trades (certified) [0.55, 0.58]
component Unskilled Labour [0.52, 0.82]
component Training / Apprenticeships (CITB) [0.47, 0.55]
component Equipment & Plant Hire [0.45, 0.78]
component Factory Manufacture (modules) [0.42, 0.30]

// Inertia: local supply of skilled labour is a CNI concern — sticky, not elastic
component Local Skilled-Labour Supply [0.38, 0.48] inertia

// ============================================================
// TIER 4 — materials, distribution, logistics
// ============================================================
// Materials pipeline: novel/low-carbon (Genesis) → recycled (Custom) →
// substitutable (Product) → raw bulk (Commodity). Wide spread is the point.
pipeline Building Materials [0.12, 0.82]
component Building Materials [0.32, 0.55]

// Distributors: traditional merchants → integrated → platform
pipeline Distributors [0.30, 0.70]
component Distributors [0.26, 0.55]

component Logistics / Freight [0.22, 0.82]

// Material supply chain itself is a CNI concern post-Brexit / post-Ukraine
component Material Supply Chain [0.18, 0.38] inertia

// ============================================================
// DEPENDENCIES — trace user anchors down to foundations
// ============================================================

// Demand side → homes / finance
Government->Homes (Private & Social)
Government->Planning & Building Regs
Government->Building Inspection / QA
Citizens (Homebuyers)->Homes (Private & Social)
Citizens (Homebuyers)->Mortgage Companies
Mortgage Companies->Homes (Private & Social)
Mortgage Companies->Building Inspection / QA

// Homes depend on construction, QA, and design
Homes (Private & Social)->Construction Mode
Homes (Private & Social)->Architecture / Blueprints
Homes (Private & Social)->Building Inspection / QA
Building Inspection / QA->Planning & Building Regs
Planning & Building Regs->Architecture / Blueprints

// Construction mode depends on labour, equipment, manufacture, materials
Construction Mode->Skilled Trades (certified)
Construction Mode->Unskilled Labour
Construction Mode->Equipment & Plant Hire
Construction Mode->Factory Manufacture (modules)
Construction Mode->Building Materials

// Labour sub-chain
Skilled Trades (certified)->Training / Apprenticeships (CITB)
Skilled Trades (certified)->Local Skilled-Labour Supply
Unskilled Labour->Local Skilled-Labour Supply
Training / Apprenticeships (CITB)->Local Skilled-Labour Supply

// Factory manufacture pulls on materials + distribution
Factory Manufacture (modules)->Building Materials
Factory Manufacture (modules)->Distributors

// Materials flow down to distribution, logistics, and the wider supply chain
Building Materials->Distributors
Distributors->Logistics / Freight
Distributors->Material Supply Chain
Logistics / Freight->Material Supply Chain

// ============================================================
// EVOLUTION ARROWS — where things are heading (12-24 months)
// ============================================================
evolve Construction Mode 0.55
evolve Factory Manufacture (modules) 0.48
evolve Building Materials 0.70
evolve Distributors 0.65
evolve Architecture / Blueprints 0.68

// ============================================================
// ANNOTATIONS — strategic observations
// ============================================================
annotation 1 [[0.62, 0.20]] Still bespoke craft: biggest industrialisation prize
annotation 2 [[0.42, 0.30]] UK MMC factory capacity thin — Ilke/Urban Splash wobbling
annotation 3 [[0.38, 0.48]] Skilled-labour supply = CNI constraint post-Brexit
annotation 4 [[0.32, 0.18]] Novel / low-carbon materials: Genesis end of pipeline
annotation 5 [[0.88, 0.55]] Homes still partly bespoke — industrialise the product
